subSubSection.paragraph:
Paravietnura insolita
sp. n. can be confused with the only other described species in the genus 
Paravietnura notabilis
sp. n., which has thick and widely sheathed long macrochaetae (distinctly thinner and narrowly sheathed in 
insolita
), an ogival labrum (non-ogival in 
insolita
), chaetae A and So2 reduced on the head (present in 
insolita
), chaetae 
L'
reduced on Abd. V (present in 
insolita
), and the furca rudimentary with minute microchaetae without chaetopores (longer microchaetae with distinct chaetopores in 
insolita
).
